Text	The ongoing 7th pandemic has affirmed that the severity of cholera is still prevalent in society , an issue recognised by the Global Task Force on Cholera Control ( GTFCC ) .	They convened a high - level meeting with officials from cholera - affected countries , donors and technical partners to announce their strategy “ The Global Roadmap to 2030 ” , an initiative to end cholera as a threat to public health by 2030 .	The three components of the strategy are : “ early detection and quick response to contain the outbreaks ; a multi-sectorial approach to prevent cholera recurrence , and , coordination of technical support and advocacy , resource mobilisation and partnership at the global level .	Category : Cholera pandemics	Category : 20th - century health disasters
